== Abstract

These are notes for **CS-GY 6043: Design and Analysis of Algorithms II**, a graduate-level
course at New York University, taught by Aaron Bernstein in Fall 2025.

This course is a continuation of Algorithms I and focuses on advanced techniques
for designing and analyzing algorithms, with strong emphasis on formal proofs,
problem-solving strategies, and mathematical rigor.

*Course description:*  
The course introduces several core tools and topics in modern algorithm design,
while further developing algorithmic problem-solving skills. Topics include
amortized analysis, potential functions, data structures such as Union-Find,
NP-completeness and reductions, approximation algorithms, randomized algorithms,
and sublinear algorithms. If time permits, additional topics such as linear
programming rounding and randomized rounding are covered.

