== Course Prerequisites

Prior completion of **CS-GY 6033 (Design and Analysis of Algorithms I)** or an
equivalent course is required. This includes familiarity with asymptotic analysis,
recurrence relations, standard sorting and searching algorithms, dynamic
programming, and fundamental graph algorithms.

Students are also expected to be comfortable with basic discrete mathematics,
including proof techniques (especially induction), graph theory, logarithms, and
elementary probability. A high level of mathematical maturity is required, as
nearly every algorithm discussed must be accompanied by a correctness proof.

